Hog really sucks in general. Even as a Orisa, I'd prefer a Dva by my side than a Hog. Even finding good hooks doesn't compensate for the rest of Dvas kit. Matrix and being able to contest high ground is so much better.

Hog sucks at mitigating damage 'cause he has no way of not feeding the other team (no matrix, no shields like Hammond, no bubbles). He is strenght is making the most out of Orisa's Halt when hooking and granting that his team will always fight with at least 1+ man advantage.
And hog distracts for the main tank by jumping in front for a second or two and drawing all of the fire. Hog also peels with hook if used correctly

Hammond also does the same thing, jumping and becoming the other team target. Rein and Orisa make space by putting barriers and pushing (or isolating areas in Orisa's case). Dva and Zarya, on the other hand, mitigate damage for the MTs when their protections are down. [2/2]

Just as a contribution. Main Tank deffinition is the one who makes space for his teammates. Off tanks are the ones who protect the space and take pressure off the MT. That's why Winston is a MT: he jumps and put a bubble, all of a sudden, all that space belongs to his team. [1/2]
